node.text:
BREAKING: The World Cup qualifier between 🇧🇷 and 🇦🇷 has been stopped after Brazilian health authorities entered the pitch, trying to escort the 4️⃣ Premier League players from Argentina off.

The Argentina players are currently in their dressing room, with their coach and captain Leo Messi discussing what’s going to happen next. 👀

node.text:
Brazilian authorities wanted to prohibit the 🇦🇷 players from the Premier League to play in tonight's World Cup qualifier due to COVID restrictions. ✋

They tried to escort Emi Martínez, Gio Lo Celso, Cristian Romero and Emi Buendía back to the airport, but after interference from the CONMEBOl, the 4️⃣ are able to start the match. [via @tycsports] 👀
